                    <head>Missal, “Helgeandshusmissal”</head>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                            <locus from="SL1" to="SL1" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="SR2" to="SR2" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                        </locusGrp>
                                        <material>Parchment</material>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="SL2" to="SL2" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="SR1" to="SR1" scheme="folios"/>
                                        </locusGrp>
                                        <note>
                                            <locus from="SL1" to="SL1" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="SR2" to="SR2" scheme="other"/> are modern parchment leaves, <locus from="SL2" to="SL2" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="SR1" to="SR1" scheme="other"/> are the original pastedowns. <locus from="Fragments_1" to="Fragments_1" scheme="other"/> are the original spine linings.</note>
                                        <dimensions type="leaf">
                                            <height quantity="210" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="130" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure type="leftFlyleaves" quantity="2" unit="folios"/>
                                    <measure type="rightFlyleaves" quantity="2" unit="folios"/>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>Modern foliation in pencil. Errors in foliation: f. 1-34, 34a, 35-123, 123a, 124-140, 140a, 141-298 (not taking into account the dummy leaves).</foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <p>
                                        <ref target="https://vceditor.library.upenn.edu/project/67505b5af5e21a0001ac77c0/viewOnly">VisColl collation</ref>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>The original quire structure consists of quinternions or quaternions with two singletons added. There are also several singletons (often in the form of slips) added to the quinternions. Quire 14 lacks 2 leaves and quire 16 lacks 1. After the modern rebinding dummy leaves haved been added to the singletons creating a new structure consisting mainly of sesternions. The viscoll collation shows the modern stucture with dummy leaves marked in blue. This collation is based on former librarian Anna Wolodarski's work.</p>
                                    <signatures>Modern quire signatures in the bottom inner margin of the first recto of each quire.</signatures>
                                    <catchwords>Catchwords in black ink in a red scroll.</catchwords>
                                </collation>
                                <condition>New flyleaves. Original flyleaves and strips used as liners for the spine bound together with the first and last quire. Original flyleaves consist of fragment from a Psalter (<locus from="SR1r" to="SR1r" scheme="folios"/> seems to be Ps. 118).</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top left corner: National Library modern ex libris.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="Note_1r" to="Note_2v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Attached to <locus from="SL1r" to="SL1r" scheme="folios"/> a handwritten note in a 18th/19th c. hand in dark ink in Latin + additions by a later hand (?) in Swedish.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true">
                                <p>Late medieval binding. Dark brown leather over wooden boards. 5 double raised bands and endbands. 2 hook-clasp fastenings. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, blind stamped <quote>A 50 a</quote>.</p>
                                <p>Original endleaves consist of fragments from a Psalter.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="225" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="165" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="120" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="tooling">
                                    <p>Blind tooling. Panel design of fillets forming lozenges and triangles.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="bookmarks">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="23" to="23" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="137" to="137" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="205" to="205" scheme="folios"/>: 3 pagemarks of tawed skin, visible at <locus from="Fore-edge" to="Fore-edge" scheme="other"/>.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <condition>Leather worn. Repaired and rebacked in the second part of the 20th century. Original endleaves and spine liners removed and bound at the front and back. Endbands visible.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100081">Sweden</placeName>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100078">Stockholm</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate when="1460">1460</origDate>. Written for the chapel of <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100282">Helgeandshuset</placeName> (Hospital of the Holy Ghost) in Stockholm.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Some time after the dissolution of <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100282">Helgeandshuset</placeName> in <date when="1531">1531,</date> the manuscript was probably transferred to<placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100281"> Stockholm Cathedral</placeName> (Storkyrkan), cf. <locus from="Note_1v" to="Note_2r" scheme="other"/> by <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100853">G.E. Klemming</persName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Acquired from the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100174">archive of the consistory of Stockholm</orgName> via <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102639">J.W. Beckman</persName> on <date when="1862-06-25"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
